-- With the gap-fill feedback, the LLM produces a complete proof that
-- includes the counting argument inline.

  yield proof-argument ≡ "**1. Loop Invariant**: At each iteration of the while loop, result[0..k] is a sorted array containing exactly the elements of multiset a[0..i] ∪ b[0..j], where k = i + j. Base case: i=0, j=0, k=0, result=[] — sorted trivially, empty ∪ empty = empty ✓. Inductive step: assume result[0..k] = sorted(a[0..i] ∪ b[0..j]). We append min(a[i], b[j]); WLOG a[i] ≤ b[j], then result[0..k+1] = sorted(a[0..i+1] ∪ b[0..j]) and k+1 = (i+1) + j ✓. **2. Sortedness Preservation**: result[k] = min(a[i], b[j]). We need result[k] ≥ result[k-1]. Case A: result[k-1] came from a, so result[k-1] = a[i-1] ≤ a[i] ≤ min(a[i], b[j]) ✓. Case B: result[k-1] came from b, so result[k-1] = b[j-1] ≤ b[j] and result[k-1] ≤ a[i] (because we didn't take a at step k-1, meaning b[j-1] ≤ a[i-1] or we were still on b), either way result[k-1] ≤ min(a[i], b[j]) ✓. **3. Permutation (with counting argument)**: Define count(x, S) as occurrences of x in multiset S. Each while-loop iteration takes exactly one element from a (incrementing i) or b (incrementing j), appending it to result. No element is created or destroyed. At loop exit: i = i_exit, j = j_exit. Remainder phase appends a[i_exit..] and b[j_exit..]. Total elements from a: a[0..i_exit] ++ a[i_exit..] = a[0..len(a)] = all of a. Similarly for b. Therefore for all x: count(x, result) = count(x, a) + count(x, b). Result is a permutation of a ++ b. **4. Termination**: i + j increases by exactly 1 each iteration (exactly one of i, j increments). Upper bound: len(a) + len(b). When i = len(a) or j = len(b), loop exits. Remaining elements appended in O(len(a) + len(b) - i - j) time. Algorithm always terminates. **5. Postcondition Discharge**: At termination, by (1) result contains all elements of a ∪ b, by (2) result is sorted, by (3) result is a permutation of a ++ b. Both postconditions — sorted ascending AND permutation of a ++ b — are established. QED."

  yield invariants ≡ [
    "At each iteration, result[0..k] is a sorted array containing exactly the elements of multiset a[0..i] ∪ b[0..j], where k = i + j. Inductive: appending min(a[i], b[j]) maintains both sortedness and the union property."
  ]

  yield termination-argument ≡ "i + j increases by exactly 1 each iteration (exactly one of i, j increments). Bounded above by len(a) + len(b). Loop exits when i = len(a) or j = len(b). The while loop always terminates."

  yield properties-proved ≡ ["sortedness", "permutation", "termination", "postcondition"]

